FBIS4-59945 "drnes097_s_94008" FBIS-NES-94-097 Daily Report 17 May 1994 Iran Two Missile Frigates Repaired, Returned to Service Two Missile Frigates Repaired, Returned to Service LD1705174994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 17 May 94 LD1705174994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Two missile frigates have been repaired and today joined the naval fleet of the Islamic Republic of Iran. The repair work on the frigates Shamshir [sword] and Zubin [javelin] was carried out by experts at factories belonging to the First Naval Zone of Iran. Also today, a reconditioned hovercraft joined Iran's First Naval Zone Armed Forces. To recondition a hovercraft, with less than 75 percent of the parts needing repair or replacement, would cost 4 million pounds [as heard] or its equivalent of hard currency in a Western country such as Britain.
